PropertyDefinitionGroup.Name: COMMON (Materials)
PropertyDefinitionGroup.Description: Collection of general properties applicable to any Building Material.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Name
PropertyDefinition.Description: Name of the material.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Category
PropertyDefinition.Description: Definition of the category (group or type) of material, in more general terms than given by attribute Name.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Description
PropertyDefinition.Description: Definition of the material in more descriptive terms than given by attributes Name or Category.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Relates To
PropertyDefinition.Description: Reference to a material relationship indicating that this material composite has parts (or constituents).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Is related with
PropertyDefinition.Description: Reference to a material relationship indicating that this material is a part (or constituent) in a material composite.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Porosity
PropertyDefinition.Description: The void fraction of the total volume occupied by material (Vbr - Vnet)/Vbr. Units: A dimensionless measure to express ratio values ranging from 0.0 to 1.0.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Mass Density
PropertyDefinition.Description: Material mass density. Usually measured in kg/m3.

PropertyDefinitionGroup.Name: COMBUSTION (Materials)
PropertyDefinitionGroup.Description: Collection of combustion-related properties applicable to Building Materials.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Specific Heat Capacity
PropertyDefinition.Description: Specific heat of the products of combustion: heat energy absorbed per temperature unit. Usually measured in J / kg Kelvin.

PropertyDefinition.Name: N2O Content
PropertyDefinition.Description: Nitrous oxide (N2O) content of the products of combustion. This is measured in weight of N2O per unit weight and is therefore unitless.

PropertyDefinition.Name: CO Content
PropertyDefinition.Description: Carbon monoxide (CO) content of the products of combustion. This is measured in weight of CO per unit weight and is therefore unitless.

PropertyDefinition.Name: CO2 Content
PropertyDefinition.Description: Carbon dioxide (CO2) content of the products of combustion. This is measured in weight of CO2 per unit weight and is therefore unitless.

PropertyDefinitionGroup.Name: THERMAL (Materials)
PropertyDefinitionGroup.Description: Collection of thermal-related properties applicable to Building Materials.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Specific Heat Capacity
PropertyDefinition.Description: Defines the specific heat of the material: heat energy absorbed per temperature unit. Usually measured in J / kg Kelvin.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Boiling Point
PropertyDefinition.Description: The boiling point of the material (fluid). Usually measured in degrees Kelvin (K).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Freezing Point
PropertyDefinition.Description: The freezing point of the material (fluid). Usually measured in degrees Kelvin (K).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Thermal Conductivity
PropertyDefinition.Description: The rate at which thermal energy is transmitted through the material. Usually measured in Watt / m Kelvin.

PropertyDefinitionGroup.Name: MECHANICAL (Materials)
PropertyDefinitionGroup.Description: Collection of mechanical-related properties applicable to Building Materials.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Dynamic Viscosity
PropertyDefinition.Description: A measure of the viscous resistance of the material. Usually measured in Pascal second (Pa s).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Young Modulus
PropertyDefinition.Description: A measure of the Young's modulus of elasticity of the material. Usually measured in N/m2.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Shear Modulus
PropertyDefinition.Description: A measure of the shear modulus of elasticity of the material. Usually measured in N/m2.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Poisson Ratio
PropertyDefinition.Description: A measure of the lateral deformations in the elastic range. A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Thermal Expansion Coefficient
PropertyDefinition.Description: A measure of the expansion coefficient for warming up the material about one Kelvin. It is usually measured in 1/K. A positive elongation per (positive) rise of temperature is expressed by a positive value.

PropertyDefinitionGroup.Name: OPTICAL (Materials)
PropertyDefinitionGroup.Description: Collection of optical-related properties applicable to Building Materials.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Visible Transmittance
PropertyDefinition.Description: Transmittance at normal incidence (visible). Defines the fraction of the visible spectrum of solar radiation that passes through per unit area, perpendicular to the surface. Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Solar Transmittance
PropertyDefinition.Description: Transmittance at normal incidence (solar). Defines the fraction of solar radiation that passes through per unit area, perpendicular to the surface. Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Thermal Transmittance
PropertyDefinition.Description: Thermal IR transmittance at normal incidence. Defines the fraction of thermal energy that passes through per unit area, perpendicular to the surface. Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Thermal Ir Emissivity Back
PropertyDefinition.Description: Thermal IR emissivity: back side. Defines the fraction of thermal energy emitted per unit area to "blackbody" at the same temperature, through the "back" side of the material. Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Thermal Ir Emissivity Front
PropertyDefinition.Description: Thermal IR emissivity: front side. Defines the fraction of thermal energy emitted per unit area to "blackbody" at the same temperature, through the "front" side of the material. Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Visible Reflectance Back
PropertyDefinition.Description: Reflectance at normal incidence (visible): back side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray in the visible spectrum that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "back" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics. Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Visible Reflectance Front
PropertyDefinition.Description: Reflectance at normal incidence (visible): front side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray in the visible spectrum that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "front" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics. Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Solar Reflectance Back
PropertyDefinition.Description: Reflectance at normal incidence (solar): back side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "back" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics. Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Solar Reflectance Front
PropertyDefinition.Description: Reflectance at normal incidence (solar): front side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "front" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics. Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

PropertyDefinitionGroup.Name: STRUCTURAL ANALYSIS DATA
PropertyDefinitionGroup.Description: Collection of Structural Analysis properties applicable to Building Materials.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Strength Grade
PropertyDefinition.Description: The quality grade of the material. Use a commonly known naming of grades of specific structural material. For Example: C25/30, S 235, etc...
